prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Fantasy Scribble Mascot Poster Style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules as concrete visual direction:
- Composition: one oversized flat mascot or object anchors the poster, with two or three smaller companion doodles orbiting it; use a white paper field, dense handmade collage balance, and visible open gaps filled by stars, rings, arrows, loops, plant stems, and tiny handwritten callouts.
- Typography: create a huge irregular hand-painted headline as part of the drawing; use thick black dry-brush letters, wobbly baselines, uneven spacing, and smaller handwritten phrases as graphic texture.
- Color: use high-saturation marker blocks with electric cyan, saturated blue, hot pink, neon lime, deep green, and small brown or purple accents; keep black outlines dominant and the white paper visible.
- Texture and lighting: flat scanned marker-and-ink treatment with marker streaks, scratchy overdraw, dirty paper texture, pressure changes, and no realistic lighting, no shadows, no gradients, and no glossy finish.
- Graphic elements: use naive fantasy mascot shapes, blunt limbs, floating eyes, patch symbols, orbit rings, starbursts, scribble fills, and intentionally awkward handmade registration.

Avoid polished vector art, anime, 3D rendering, photorealism, platform UI, watermarks, logos, creator signatures, QR codes, exact source wording, exact source character silhouettes, and the original source story arrangement.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
